f the coronavirus outbreak after the clubs rejected the possibility of playing matches behind closed doors. Switzerland, which has had at least two dozen confirmed cases, introduced a ban on Friday on events expected to draw 1,000 people or more until March 15. It said it was an effort to combat the coronavirus. In response, the Swiss League called off all matches in the top two divisions and Saturday and Sunday. It has now extended the ban to the international break at the end of March.(Reuters/NAN) VANGUARD UEFA on Wednesday overwhelmingly elected Slovenian lawyer Aleksander Ceferin, almost unknown three months ago, as its new president to lead the world's most powerful football confederation into a new era after Michel Platini was forced to resign. September 14, 2016 In "Sports" Jose Mourinho should be given a warm welcome when the Manchester United manager returns to Chelsea, on Sunday said present Blues incumbent Antonio Conte. October 21, 2016 In "News" UEFA will reportedly hold emergency talks this week amid concerns the coronavirus outbreak could lead to postponements or even cancellations in this season's Champions League or Euro 2020. European football's governing body is understood to be seeking talks with all 55 member associations at the annual congress in Amsterdam. UEFA… March 1, 2020 In "Sports"